  "prompt": "What are the best web design firms in New York?",
  "response": "While determining the \"best\" web design firms can be subjective and depends on specific needs and preferences, several New York-based firms have consistently received recognition for their high-quality work, innovation, and client satisfaction. Here are some noteworthy web design firms in New York:\n\n1. **Blue Fountain Media**: Known for its digital marketing and web design services, Blue Fountain Media has worked with prominent brands like NASA, Sony, and P&G.\n\n2. **Ruckus Marketing**: This full-service agency specializes in web design, branding, and digital marketing, catering to clients like BMW, HarperCollins, and Hearst.\n\n3. **Big Drop Inc.**: Renowned for its creative web design and development services, Big Drop Inc. has collaborated with clients like Samsung, CitiBank, and Assurant.\n\n4. **Crafted**: With a focus on custom web design and branding, Crafted has partnered with various sectors, providing highly tailored digital experiences.\n\n5. **Taktical Digital**: Offering web design along with performance-based marketing services, Taktical Digital boasts a portfolio that includes WeWork, BarkBox, and various startups.\n\n6. **BMG Media Co.**: This firm specializes in web design and development, focusing on creating custom solutions for businesses of all sizes.\n\n7. **eDesign Interactive**: Known for their creative web design and digital marketing strategies, eDesign Interactive has worked with brands like Vodafone and Dell.\n\n8. **DotcomWeavers**: A web design and eCommerce development firm with a strong track record, DotcomWeavers has created solutions for clients like Uni-ball and The Diamond Seller.\n\n9. **Lounge Lizard**: This agency provides web design, development, and marketing services, and has worked with brands like Canon, Sony, and ESPN.\n\n10. **Maxburst**: Focusing on web design and digital marketing, Maxburst has helped businesses like JetBlue and Suffolk Federal adapt and thrive online.\n\nWhen choosing a web design firm, it's essential to consider your specific needs, budget, and the firm's expertise in your industry. Reviewing their portfolios, client testimonials, and case studies can also provide valuable insights into their capabilities and alignment with your project goals.",
